transliteration: Doust Hartaasristkartaa Jagad Mai Jih Gadth||
translation: He is Vanquisher of the tyrants and the Creator of the universe, and His Story is being narrated in the whole world.

transliteration: Bhoot Bhab(i) Bhavikkh Bhavaan Pramaan Dev Agadj||
translation: He, the Invincible Lord, is the same in the Past, Present and Future.

transliteration: Aadh Ant Anaadh Sree Pat(i) Param Purakh Abhanj||12||192||
translation: He, the Lord of maya, the Immortal and unassailable Supreme Purusha, was there in the beginning and will be there at the end.12.192.

gurmukhi: Drm ky Ankrm jyqk kIn qaun pswr ]
transliteration: Dharam Ke Ankaram Jetak Koon Taoun Pasaar||
translation: He hath spread all the other religious practices.

transliteration: Dev Adev Gaddhrah Kinnar Machchh Kachchh Apaar||
translation: He hath Created innumerable gods, demons, Gandharvas, Kinnars, fish incarnations and tortoise incarnations.

transliteration: Bhoom Akaas Jale Thale Maih Maanooai Jih Naam||
translation: His Name is reverently repeated by the beings on earth, in sky, in water and on land.

transliteration: Doust Hartaa Poust Kartaa Sristtee Hartaa Kaam||13||193||
translation: His works include the decimation of tyrants, giving of strength (to the saints) and support to the world.13.193.

transliteration: Doust Harnaa Srist Karnaa Diaal Laal Gobind||
translation: The Beloved Merciful Lord is the Vanquisher of the tyrants and the Creator of the Universe.

transliteration: Mittra Paalak Sattra Dhaalak Deen Dyaal Moukand||

transliteration: Aghau Danndan Doust Khanndan Kaal Hoon Ke Kaal||
translation: He, the Merciful Lord of the lowely, He is the punisher of the sinners and destroyer of the tyrants; He is the decimater even of death.

transliteration: Doust Haranan Poust Karanan Sarab Ke Pratipaal||14||194||
translation: He is the Vanquisher of the tyrants, giver of strength (to the saints) and the Sustainer of all.14.194.

transliteration: Sarab Kartaa Sarab Hartaa Sarab Te Ankaam||

transliteration: Sarab Khanndan Sarab Danndan Sarab Ke Nij Bhaam||

transliteration: Sarab Bhougtaa Sarab Jougtaa Sarab Karam Prabeen||
